The Nigerian Meteorological Agency (NIMET) has predicted that a high chance of a possible rise in temperature across most northern cities in Nigeria. According to a statement issued by the NiMet, in its High-Temperature Outlook. most parts of the Northern States and parts of Niger and Kwara in the central States are expected to experience temperatures greater than 40°C. N CASE YOU MISSED THESE FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE  Few places in the South including parts of Oyo, Ogun, Osun, and Ekiti are expected to record temperatures between 35°C to 40°C. The statement noted that as a result, there are chances of experiencing high thermal discomfort in parts of Kebbi, Dutse, Bauchi, and Jalingo while other areas may experience cold mornings, the statement warned against the occurrence of heatstroke, sunstroke, muscle cramp, and fatigue.